-- Modec Venture Signs $1.125 Billion Loan With Five Japanese Banks
-- B y   E m i   U r a b e
-- 2012-03-28T07:00:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-28/modec-venture-signs-1-125-billion-loan-with-five-japanese-banks.html
A venture owned by  Modec Inc. (6269) ,
Mitsui & Co., Mitsui O.S.K. Lines Ltd. and Marubeni Corp. signed
a $1.125 billion loan to build a vessel for exploring the
Cernabi South oilfield off  Brazil .  The lenders are Bank of Tokyo-Mitsubishi UFJ Ltd., Sumitomo
Mitsui Banking Corp., Mizuho Corporate Bank Ltd., Sumitomo
Trust & Banking Co., and the government-run Japan Bank for
International Cooperation.  The loan was disclosed in a statement from the Japan Bank
for International Cooperation.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Emi Urabe in Tokyo at 
 eurabe@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
